==English==
===Etymology 1===
From Latin [[rosa]], ''[[rose]]'', from ancient Greek [[ρόδον]] (''rodon'') "a flow of scent", from [[ροή]] (''roe'') "flow" + [[οδμή]] (''odme'') "scent".

====Adjective====
'''rosy'''

# [[rose-coloured]]
# [[optimistic]]

=====Related terms=====
*[[rose]]

===Etymology 2===
From Cockney rhyming slang, "Rosie Lee".
====Alternative spellings====
* [[Rosie]] (more common spelling, as per the etymology)
====Noun====
'''Rosy'''
#(''British English, slang'') tea
#:I wish a cup of Rosy.

